00:49:58.350 --> 00:49:59.630
the denominator.

00:49:59.630 --> 00:50:03.690
Or rather, this one dominates
the denominator.

00:50:03.690 --> 00:50:12.740
And now you have something of
the form k1 A times M. This

00:50:12.740 --> 00:50:14.830
dominates, this term
goes away.

00:50:14.830 --> 00:50:19.760
The k2 goes away and you have
k1 times A times M left over

00:50:19.760 --> 00:50:25.270
as the rate of the reaction.

00:50:25.270 --> 00:50:25.970
Second order.

00:50:25.970 --> 00:50:27.040
There are two species here.

00:50:27.040 --> 00:50:30.290
A times M. M could be A or it
could be some chaperone.

00:50:30.290 --> 00:50:31.290
A squared.

00:50:31.290 --> 00:50:33.000
Second order process.

00:50:33.000 --> 00:50:34.790
So if you're at low
pressure, you see

00:50:34.790 --> 00:50:35.740
